comment_regular_data.body: Closing this for now, as it's nowhere near ready for merging.
how long would it take for newgroupchats could be merged?
@Renha minutes, once a working tests suite is confirmed to be working.

Btw, guys, I almost done fully-compatible-with-old-groupchats-and-api upgrade to old groupchats. This upgrade let clients keep history of groupchats and restore groupchats after clients (even all) restarts. So, should I make PR, or you will answer me "Hey, new groupchats almost done, don't touch old ones"?
Anyway, next version of Isotoxin will be able to keep groupchat history and restore groupchats after restart
New group chats have been almost done for 2 years, so go ahead and make a PR. Are you using the new conference API?

> Are you using the new conference API?

yes

> so go ahead and make a PR

ok, I will create PR soon (about a week)
@isotoxin You can describe how you implement it?
@isotoxin do you have moderators/administrators management, etc?

> @isotoxin do you have moderators/administrators management, etc?

I'm my own person (as I understand your question)

@quininer

> @isotoxin You can describe how you implement it?

Main: current (aka old) groupchats have unique ID. That is almost it! I just get access to this ID.
I can't describe other changes for now due some of them are on research stage. All changes will be described in PR
